WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:00.840
CHAPTER VII.

00:09.380 --> 00:14.900
My son, keep my words, and lay up my commandments with thee.

00:15.140 --> 00:19.920
Keep my commandments and live, and my law as the apple of thine eye.

00:21.220 --> 00:25.500
Bind them upon thy fingers, write them upon the table of thine heart.

00:25.500 --> 00:31.220
Say unto wisdom, thou art my sister, and call understanding thy kinswoman,

00:31.880 --> 00:34.940
that they may keep thee from the strange woman,

00:35.280 --> 00:38.440
from the stranger which flattereth with her words.

00:38.980 --> 00:42.980
For at the window of my house I looked through my casement,

00:43.460 --> 00:48.440
and beheld among the simple ones I discerned among the youths

00:48.440 --> 00:50.820
a young man void of understanding.

00:50.820 --> 00:54.960
Passing through the street near her corner, he went the way to her house.

00:56.420 --> 01:00.660
In the twilight, in the evening, in the black and dark night.

01:01.180 --> 01:04.980
And behold, there met him a woman, with the attire of an harlot,

01:05.480 --> 01:06.740
and subtle of heart.

01:07.340 --> 01:11.200
She is loud and stubborn, her feet abide not in her house.

01:11.580 --> 01:16.300
Now is she without, now in the streets, and lieth in wait at every corner.

01:16.300 --> 01:21.680
So she caught him, and kissed him, and with an impudent face said unto him,

01:22.000 --> 01:26.800
I have peace offerings with me, this day have I paid my vows.

01:27.420 --> 01:31.900
Therefore came I forth to meet thee, diligently to seek thy face,

01:32.100 --> 01:33.540
and I have found thee.

01:33.880 --> 01:37.160
I have decked my bed with coverings of tapestry,

01:37.540 --> 01:40.760
with carved works, with fine linen of Egypt.

01:41.080 --> 01:45.120
I have perfumed my bed with myrrh, aloes, and cinnamon.

01:45.120 --> 01:49.520
Come, let us take our fill of love until the morning.

01:49.920 --> 01:52.620
Let us solace ourselves with loves.

01:53.540 --> 01:57.520
For the good man is not at home, he has gone a long journey.

01:57.900 --> 02:00.100
He hath taken a bag of money with him,

02:00.440 --> 02:03.180
and will come home at the day appointed.

02:03.500 --> 02:07.400
With her much fair speech, she caused him to yield.

02:08.100 --> 02:10.820
With the flattering of her lips she forced him,

02:11.180 --> 02:13.240
he goeth after her straightway.

02:13.660 --> 02:16.000
As an ox goeth to the slaughter,

02:16.640 --> 02:19.860
or as a fool to the correction of the stocks,

02:20.460 --> 02:22.520
till a dart strike through his liver,

02:22.960 --> 02:25.420
as a bird hasteth to the snare,

02:26.120 --> 02:28.820
and knoweth not that it is for his life.

02:29.720 --> 02:32.640
Harken unto me now therefore, oh ye children,

02:33.280 --> 02:35.660
and attend to the words of my mouth.

02:36.040 --> 02:38.280
Let not thine heart decline to her ways,

02:38.720 --> 02:40.620
go not astray in her paths,

02:40.620 --> 02:43.580
for she hath cast down many wounded,

02:44.000 --> 02:48.020
yea, many strong men have been slain by her.

02:48.600 --> 02:51.140
Her house is the way to hell,

02:51.520 --> 02:55.540
going down to the chambers of death.

